&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GLG is seeking an experienced professional for the role of Compliance Senior Analyst in our Shanghai office. The individual will be part of GLG’s 70+ person global compliance department and would be required to provide timely and thoughtful support for business colleagues. In this role you will develop strong actionable business skills – including time management, prioritization, communication, negotiation, problem solving, and project management.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;GLG attracts employees from diverse academic and professional backgrounds. We look for individuals who are passionate about our mission to transform how professionals learn and who embody GLG’s values: learning and curiosity, responsibility, courage, judgment, fresh perspective, service, and integrity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Screening and Resolutions: Conduct thorough screening of expert profiles to ensure completeness, accuracy, and appropriateness. Identify, assess, manage, and report risks in a timely manner. Collaborate with internal stakeholders to effectively resolve identified screening issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team Collaboration: Work closely with the Gurugram and Regional Compliance teams to solve daily screening challenges using proven best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surveillance: Assist with the firm’s compliance surveillance program by reviewing expert engagements against the GLG Compliance Framework. Identify “red flags” and policy violations, navigating issues that require deep-dive assessment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process Improvement: Identify areas for improvement and recommend changes to compliance procedures and standards where appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder Engagement: Serve as the primary point of contact for internal client service professionals on queries related to China-based experts; provide prompt, accurate guidance on policy interpretation and day-to-day inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Problem Solving: Apply a solution-oriented approach to complex compliance issues under tight deadlines. Provide thoughtful analysis and risk assessments when escalating complex matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training: Assist with or lead internal team training and strategic initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: Graduate/Postgraduate with 1 years of minimum relevant industry experience in Compliance, Legal, Risk Management or a related field is required. Candidates with a legal background will be prioritized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research Skills: Possess excellent internet-based research skills, with proven experience utilizing advanced search operators and public databases (such as Tianyancha, China Judgments Online, and China Enforcement Information Disclosure Network) considered a strong advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical Thinking: Demonstrated ability to use logic and reasoning to identify the strengths and weaknesses of solutions or approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Language Proficiency: Full professional fluency in both English and Mandarin (written and verbal) is mandatory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational Excellence: Proven ability to multi-task and prioritize a high volume of requests in a fast-paced environment without sacrificing attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpersonal Impact: Strong communication skills with the ability to build relationships based on mutual trust and respect.&lt;/li&gt;
