&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GLG is seeking a motivated and enthusiastic individual to join our office in Seoul as a Project Support Specialist. Project Support Specialists (PSS) are responsible for arranging connections between GLG’s clients and selected experts in our Network, global key opinion leaders and senior industry executives acting in a consultative capacity. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To facilitate these engagements, the PSS will work closely with both client-facing GLG Research professionals and GLG’s sophisticated client base, which ranges from hedge fund managers to partners at private equity firms and project managers at top-tier consulting firms and Fortune 1000 companies.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a PSS, you will develop a deep understanding of GLG’s business model and end-client markets as well as acquire incredible client service experience in a dynamic, high-intensity environment. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Position Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate interactions between GLG clients and requested experts in GLG Network&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate requests with complex compliance requirements and client-specific preferences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and build strong working relationships with Client Solutions partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successfully execute against project objectives, seeing each project through to completion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align with and develop deep understanding of a specific end-client market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Appreciate the urgency of competing projects and prioritize accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate adaptability in a fast-paced, dynamic work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Position Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent in communication and interaction skills, including demonstrated oral, written and presentation abilities in a business-focused setting using a variety of communication channels (telephone, e-mail etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0-2 years of work experience preferably working as executive assistant &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in Korean and Business level proficiency in English and other languages are plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preferred Qualifications &amp;amp; Skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek bright, positive and flexible people who also:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act with the highest integrity and professionalism in all their endeavours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think creatively and focus on opportunities for growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Express a strong desire to work in a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability and initiative to handle increasing responsibility over time &lt;/li&gt;
